Convergence of Neural RDMs

How many neural RDMs do we need?

Stephen Mazurchuk https://www.mcw.edu/education/medical-scientist-training-program/people/stephen-mazurchuk (Medical College of Wisconsin)https://www.mcw.edu/
2022-01-14

In the current CAT study there are 18 subjects with all sessions. At Leo’s request I calculated the correlation between the average neural RDM and the CREA RDM where the neural RDM was derived from all the vertices within the ALE mask from the 2009 paper.

The result was that for the 18 subjects in CAT, the correlation was .355! Keep in mind, this is a correlation between 44,850 data points. For the SOE study with 34 subjects, the correlation was .389 (51,040 data points)!

I think this is a very impressive result, and it also made me wonder

Are additional subjects adding more signal to the neural RDM?

This question is effectively asking how many subjects should be scanned. Perhaps the correlation between the average neural RDM and CREA plateaus after 20 subjects and additional subjects have little effect.

The question of how many subjects to include is common one, and I expect it to be highly depedent on the details of each experiment. For our data, I think that the most relevant details are:

  • Rapid event-related design, many conditions
  • Single word presentations
    • 6 presentations of each word

Assessing the Convergence

In answering this question, I used the same semantic mask referenced above. Shown below is the ALE mask thresheld at > .95.

Then using the vertices within this mask, calculated how well a random subset of subjects correlated with CREA. This results in the following plot.

Thoughts

In interpreting the above plot, the convergence as the number of subjects increases is somewhat of an artifact of there only being 34 subjects. All subsets of 32 subjects look quite similar (at most differing by two people). Thus, we really can’t estimate how much more there is to grow. However, some points that do seem clear are that:

There is a major improvement from 10 subjects to 20 subjects

and secondly

There is some improvement from 20 subjects to 30

Hopefully once I have all 40 subjects proccessed we can get a better estimate of how much additional subjects help!
